INSERT INTO public.raw_items VALUES (619, 19, 'tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-3277310055963332196.post-5347616737523931145', 'scheduled', 'https://www.nhltraderumors.me/2026/01/roman-josi-trade-rumors-sharks-predators.html', 'https://www.nhltraderumors.me/2026/01/roman-josi-trade-rumors-sharks-predators.html', 'NHL Rumors: Sharks Linked To Potential Blockbuster Trade With Predators', '<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiH-vaIb-Jx0XvgYRbmenU39O2zMOqLwM0C_LttM2RWlepfbu52_y1CtdNRE4BPl4uaR8qfjZQZmJ0hyphenhyphenUr0d_MwrqSP8-wrhQfmMou1vs3fJj8_1Kax3KS2LGIPdQhiA_xi7GwIXCYtAE2L4usFK6p-AZ-2js3_LYjBVv1ylA9cgVO9xHCCMg7oTzpompDs/s4754/USATSI_28065689.jpg" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img alt="Nashville Predators defenseman Roman Josi handles the puck during 2026 game." border="0" height="266" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiH-vaIb-Jx0XvgYRbmenU39O2zMOqLwM0C_LttM2RWlepfbu52_y1CtdNRE4BPl4uaR8qfjZQZmJ0hyphenhyphenUr0d_MwrqSP8-wrhQfmMou1vs3fJj8_1Kax3KS2LGIPdQhiA_xi7GwIXCYtAE2L4usFK6p-AZ-2js3_LYjBVv1ylA9cgVO9xHCCMg7oTzpompDs/w400-h266/USATSI_28065689.jpg" title="Nashville Predators defenseman Roman Josi handles the puck during 2026 game." width="400" /></a></div><br /><div>Jeff Marek’s <span><a href="https://x.com/thesheethockey/status/2013768213914411221">The Sheet</a></span> tossed gasoline on the rumor mill this week when the show kicked around a true blockbuster idea: the <a href="https://www.nhltraderumors.me/search/label/San%20Jose%20Sharks">San Jose Sharks</a> calling the <a href="https://www.nhltraderumors.me/search/label/Nashville%20Predators">Nashville Predators</a> about Roman Josi.&nbsp;</div><div><p>It wasn’t framed as a sure thing, but more as the kind of swing a team takes when it’s ready to level up fast, and Greg Wyshynski on the show put it bluntly by asking if San Jose should be “knocking” on Nashville’s door if the Predators unravel. Drew Remenda’s answer leaned into a more patient approach in the conversation.</p>
INSERT INTO public.raw_items VALUES (620, 19, 'tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-3277310055963332196.post-4199930746938864189', 'scheduled', 'https://www.nhltraderumors.me/2026/01/maple-leafs-could-become-sellers-trade-deadline.html', 'https://www.nhltraderumors.me/2026/01/maple-leafs-could-become-sellers-trade-deadline.html', 'NHL Rumors: Maple Leafs To Start Selling?', '<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhhcb1v6Ej69DuWCkhv79Ep7TB3blOST7OhXFTB94PkJhZV2T7XuNuk1SaRZeAwpW5XrZwtPMIWbWkrx2wzcNiebOaK02D0SRQ5lSn5_6Rq-OAWna57YssSoUsL3zl0Nj5FXX6pcmFxA9UkeGfXlZJ3mzD9ZzeKSIADTJatrXcIW3Jg0UVnqiebn6-EgZyh/s2724/USATSI_28072661.jpg" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img alt="Toronto Maple Leafs head Coach Craig Berube reacts during 2026 game." border="0" height="280" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhhcb1v6Ej69DuWCkhv79Ep7TB3blOST7OhXFTB94PkJhZV2T7XuNuk1SaRZeAwpW5XrZwtPMIWbWkrx2wzcNiebOaK02D0SRQ5lSn5_6Rq-OAWna57YssSoUsL3zl0Nj5FXX6pcmFxA9UkeGfXlZJ3mzD9ZzeKSIADTJatrXcIW3Jg0UVnqiebn6-EgZyh/w400-h280/USATSI_28072661.jpg" title="Toronto Maple Leafs head Coach Craig Berube reacts during 2026 game." width="400" /></a></div><br /><div>Toronto came into this homestand looking like a team that might add, but the slide has flipped the conversation quickly.&nbsp;</div><div><p>With the <a href="https://www.nhltraderumors.me/search/label/Toronto%20Maple%20Leafs">Maple Leafs</a> falling further out of the wild card picture and the deadline clock getting louder, league chatter is starting to sound like it might be time for the team to start considering selling.&nbsp;</p><p>The vibe around the market is shifting toward Toronto selling pieces, and the longer the skid lingers, the more obvious that path becomes. <span></span></p>
